                <div class="field-content"><h2>The State of Play of Chinese Policy and Bilateral Issues</h2>

<p>The Obama administration‚Äôs fourth major meeting with China, involving multiple Cabinet Secretaries and Chinese Ministers, the <a href="http://www.state.gov/r/pa/prs/dpb/2012/04/188322.htm">Strategic and Economic Dialogue</a> (S&ED), will be held <a href="http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2012-04/23/c_131545765.htm">May 3 and 4</a> in Beijing. As usual, the U.S. delegation will be lead by Secretaries Clinton and Geithner, and their Chinese hosts will be Vice Premier Wang Qishan (who focuses on economic policy) and State Councilor Dai Bingguo (responsible for foreign policy).</p></div>
