  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>President Obama and his team look like they‚Äôve had  a productive day in Beijing, even if Press Secretary Robert Gibbs <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/11/17/AR2009111700545.html?hpid=topnews">had to remind the media</a> that the Obama team was not expecting &#8220;that the waters would part and everything would change over our almost two-and-a-half day trip to China.&#8221;  The just-released <a href="../library/us-china-joint-statement-november-17th">U.S.-China Joint Statement</a> is almost encyclopedic in its coverage of the challenges facing these two world leaders, with commitments to work together more closely on them.</p></div>
